title: Blue Origin flies six on first New Shepard suborbital flight of 2022
summary: Blue Origin launched its New Shepard suborbital vehicle on its first flight of the year March 31, carrying six people on a brief trip to space and back.

title: Blue Origin flies fourth suborbital crew mission
summary: Blue Origin’s New Shepard suborbital launcher lofted six passengers, including the rocket’s chief designer, on an up-and-down flight to the edge of space Thursday.

title: Starlink eyes Southeast Asia foothold with the Philippines
summary: The Philippines is set to become the first country in Southeast Asia to access SpaceX’s Starlink broadband services, its government announced March 31.

title: Coverage Set for Axiom Mission 1 Briefings, Events, Broadcast
summary: NASA and Axiom Space will provide coverage of the upcoming prelaunch and launch activities for Axiom Mission 1 (Ax-1), the first private astronaut mission to the International Space Station.

title: Slingshot wins $25 million Space Force contract to develop digital twin of the space environment
summary: Slingshot Aerospace won a $25.2 million Space Force contract to develop a virtual replica of the space environment

title: Chinese spacecraft reenters atmosphere ahead of new space station missions
summary: China deorbited the Tianzhou-2 cargo spacecraft Thursday after testing on-orbit docking, refueling and module transposition for the Chinese space station.

title: Blue Origin launches NS-20 suborbital crew mission
summary: Blue Origin has sent another crew of six to space with the launch of their fourth crewed mission in the company’s history. The flight took place from Blue Origin’s West Texas facility in Van Horn, with liftoff occurring on Thursday, March 31 at 8:58 AM CDT (13:58 UTC).

title: SES to work with NorthStar on space situational awareness
summary: Satellite operator SES announced March 31 it is working with Canadian startup NorthStar Earth & Space on developing space situational awareness (SSA) data products to support its fleet of communications satellites.

title: SpaceX rolls upgraded Super Heavy booster to the launch pad
summary: SpaceX has begun transporting an upgraded Super Heavy booster to its South Texas launch facilities, where the rocket will likely be tested...

title: Northrop Grumman weighing options for new Artemis lunar lander competition
summary: Northrop Grumman says it’s still considering whether to rejoin a Blue Origin-led team for a second Artemis lunar lander competition or to go on its own.
